body.description: Tiny tastes, fresh firsts. Safely introduce baby to new food with Dr. Browns, fresh firsts silicone whole food feeder. Help baby begin transitioning to whole foods with the Fresh Firsts Silicone Whole Food Feeder, featuring tiny holes that let just enough food through for baby to safely self-feed. The silicone feeder is soft yet durable and bite-resistant and can hold anything from fresh food to frozen treats-which also makes it a great teether. Lightweight and easy for little hands to hold, the mesh-free design makes for less mess while baby is learning new eating skills. The silicone whole food feeder's features an ergonomic shape perfect for little mouths. Dishwasher safe (top rack). BPA free.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I’m a big fan! And so is my baby!
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Got this in and opened it up right away and washed it so I could let my teething 6.5 month old get some relief. She LOVED it. It was easy for her to hold onto. The silicone is a perfect texture and it was super easy to clean. I put 4 or so blueberries in it and squished it ever so slightly to get some of the juices out so she could taste it better initially and she instantly was all about it. Entertained her for a good 15 min or so. Will be a great way to get them teething relief while also letting them enjoy trying new foods!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A favorite for my baby
reviews.reviewText: We love this product. It is easy for me to fill with fruit, yogurt, purees etc. and then I stick it in the freezer for a few hours. Very easy to clean with a rinse or in the dishwasher. My son can easily hold it and get whatever is inside it into his mouth. He especially loves it when he has a new tooth coming in. I only use it in the kitchen when he is in his high chair to avoid a choking hazard or a mess. Once it starts to melt it does get a bit messy. Will reuse with my next child.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Work great! Good quality.
reviews.reviewText: As pictured. They work great and are good quality. They are easy to clean and are WAY easier to clean than the other net mesh ones I have. You can just run them underwater to clean them. The only part that kind of gets food stuck in it is the part where you screw on the top. There isn’t a ton of room to put food in the mesh cap but enough for a baby.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for trying solids!
reviews.reviewText: I love this for my baby! Perfect for introducing new foods easily, and safely. It squeezes out the holes just enough to want to keep trying more, but not an overwhelming amount at a time. Easy to hold & easy to get food out. Also very easy to store, load, & prep for later & to clean. I love the rubber for the little baby gums to soothe too. Not hard or aggressive. The shape holds up well- unlike other types of feeders I’ve tried that are mesh and get soft and just flop all over and are hard for the babies to actually eat. Minimal mess with this one as well. Love that it has a lid to close up and store for later. No complaints with this product! Easy to help them feed & they can hold on their own too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great first foods tool/ silicone stains easily
reviews.reviewText: These are great to put frozen fruit or ice chips for baby’s first foods/ teething. They are easy to assemble/ dissemble, made durable, and easy to clean. The only thing is they are a little bulky for baby to hold and stain very easily especially with (peach , mango).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Loved the size, baby can easily grab the handle. Cleans up very well. Much better than the mesh alternatives. Very secure with the screw on/off top. Fits a decent size strawberry and the cap is perfect to keep it clean. 🤌

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lifesaver for teething baby
reviews.reviewText: I shove the end of a banana in this, avocado, mashed berries, basically anything the baby can eat for her age and she loves it. It really helps with teething and she gnaws on it for maybe 20 minutes. She won't eat much when she's teething, so once she chews on this for a while, her gums aren't hurting as bad and she'll eat. Worth every penny.

reviews.reviewTitle: Use With Pieces of Food, NOT Puree
reviews.reviewText: There is a video going around on TikTok of a woman who throws these in the garbage because they're messy and doesn't understand why you don't just use a spoon to feed your kid purees.These are not to be used with puree (although you still can) you put chunks of food in them so that your baby can safely taste new foods without you having to puree them. They are fantastic! I like to put things I normally wouldn't puree in them, such as cucumbers or bell peppers.Another thing I do is freeze purees in small ice cube trays, and then put those small frozen cubes in here. They're not as messy that way and they are great for a teething baby.Also, I really prefer these silicone ones over the mesh ones. The mesh gets kinda rough and stained over time. They are also very difficult to clean, these I just put in the dishwasher.I highly recommend. I used them for two of three kids (first kid we used the mesh ones) and I've boughten some as baby gifts as well.
